10/10/2010
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Defence Minister Costas Papacostas announced on Friday (October 8th) that the country has destroyed another 494 anti-personnel land mines as part of obligations under the Ottawa Mine Ban treaty it signed in 1997.
The mines were destroyed at a ceremony at Kalo Chorio, which was attended by Papacostas.
According to the minister, 48,475 stockpiled mines have been destroyed since July 2007, with the island scheduled to get rid of 2,183 more by July 1st 2013.
(Cyprus Mail - 09/10/10;
AP - 08/10/10)
